what is regression testing?regression testing is a type of software testing that seeks to uncover new software bugs
in existing functional and non-functional areas of a system after changes

have been made to it. why is regression testing important?regression testing is important because it helps ensure that changes to a system do not introduce new bugs or regressions. by retesting areas of a system that were previously working correctly

regression testing can help ensure that these areas continue to work correctly after changes have been made. what are some common regression testing techniques?there are many different regression testing techniques
but some common ones include retesting all or part of the system

and automating tests. what are some challenges with regression testing?some challenges with regression testing include the time and effort required to retest the entire system or selected parts of it after each change
the need for good test coverage in order to identify regressions early
and the difficulty of creating effective test cases that can find regressions.
